===========================================
CLOUD DEPLOYMENT EXCLUSION
===========================================

This software is designed exclusively for deployment on operator-controlled
infrastructure -- bare metal servers under the operator's physical control, or
virtual machines on hypervisors the operator owns and operates. It is NOT
designed, supported, or recommended for cloud-based instances, VPS, IaaS, or
shared hosting where the operator does not control the physical hardware,
hypervisor, and network infrastructure. The installer blocks installation on
detected cloud providers. Cloud deployments receive NO SUPPORT and the authors
accept NO LIABILITY for any consequences of cloud deployment. See WARNINGS.md
and TERMS.md (Section 5B) for complete details.

===========================================
ARM ARCHITECTURE
===========================================

This software has NOT been tested on ARM architecture (including Raspberry Pi,
ARM64/aarch64, and ARMv7). All packages and binary dependencies target x86_64
(amd64) on Ubuntu 24.04 LTS. ARM deployments are NOT supported. See WARNINGS.md
and TERMS.md (Section 5C) for complete details.

===========================================
TOR NETWORK FUNCTIONALITY
===========================================

This software includes optional Tor (The Onion Router) functionality, disabled
by default. Tor is configured as a client only — it does not operate as a relay,
exit node, or bridge. Use of Tor may be restricted or prohibited in some
jurisdictions. See WARNINGS.md and TERMS.md (Section 5A) for complete legal
notices, user acknowledgments, and liability disclaimers regarding Tor.

